ZH: 这是我奶奶的遗照，让我想起了她。
EN: This is a photo of my grandmother which reminds me of her.

ZH: 他们把父亲的遗照放在了墙上。
EN: They put their father's photo on the wall.

ZH: 每次看到儿子的遗照，他的父亲都会流泪。
EN: Every time he sees his son's photo, his father would shed tears.

ZH: 她保留了丈夫的遗照，用来怀念他。
EN: She kept her husband's photo, using it to remember him.

ZH: 遗照上的笑容总是让我感到安慰。
EN: The smile on the photo always gives me comfort.

ZH: 那张遗照是我家曾祖父的。
EN: That photo is of my great-grandfather.

ZH: 藏起了妻子的遗照，他仍然每天思念她。
EN: He hides his wife's photo and still misses her every day.

ZH: 她把孩子的遗照放在枕边，以便每晚都可以看到他。
EN: She puts her child's photo by her pillow so she can see him every night.

ZH: 父亲的遗照里面有我小时候的回忆。
EN: My childhood memories are inside my father's photo.

ZH: 每次回家，我都会看爷爷的遗照。
EN: Every time I come home, I would look at my grandfather's photo.

ZH: 遗照带给我对故人的思念。
EN: The photo evokes my longing for the deceased.

ZH: 我把朋友的遗照放在书桌上，以便常常看见他。
EN: I put my friend's photo on the desk so that I can see him often.

ZH: 这张遗照记录了一段美好的回忆。
EN: This photo captures a beautiful memory.

ZH: 我常常拿着妈妈的遗照安慰自己。
EN: I often hold my mother's photo to comfort myself.

ZH: 那个遗照是我让我想起了小时候的梦想。
EN: That photo reminds me of my childhood dreams.

ZH: 我很怀念这副遗照上的人。
EN: I miss the person in this photo very much.

ZH: 这个遗照带给我温暖的回忆。
EN: This photo brings warm memories to me.

ZH: 我从遗照上看到了自己的影子。
EN: I can see my own reflection in the photo.

ZH: 遗照是一种重要的精神寄托。
EN: The photo is an important spiritual sustenance.

ZH: 遗照是我宝贵的回忆。
EN: The photo is my precious memory.
